                'en' => 'Jehovah\'s Witnesses are a global Christian religious organization that traces its origins to the Bible Student movement in the United States in the 1870s. This faith is characterized by its non-Trinitarian beliefs, asserting that God, whom they call Jehovah, is supreme, and Jesus Christ is his Son and agent, not part of a triune Godhead. Witnesses are best recognized globally for their intensive, organized evangelism, often conducted door-to-door or at literature stands in public places. They disseminate religious publications, primarily *The Watchtower* and *Awake!*, translated into over 1,000 languages. A core doctrine is the belief that humanity is living in the "last days" leading up to Armageddon, which will usher in God\'s Kingdom. Their practices stress strict separation from secular government, leading to refusal to salute national flags, participate in military service, or vote in public elections. Furthermore, they abstain from blood transfusions on religious grounds and do not celebrate traditional holidays or birthdays, viewing them as pagan accretions.',
